Description_lang: A partnership with the island nation of Kul Tiras would grant us access to their legendary navy... and a military edge over the Horde.
Help Brann Bronzebeard lead an expedition into the dark forests of Nazmir, in search of the lost Captain Conrad. Beware the blood trolls.
Trade Prince Gallywix has received reports of a large Azerite deposit in Drustvar. You are his escort.
If they can storm into the Undercity, then we can assault Stormwind. It's time to go get our soldiers back.
The desert of Vol'dun has a promising harbor for our fleet. First, however, we must deal with the indigenous snake people known as the sethrak.
Rexxar has already established an outpost in Stormsong Valley, but his forces have been surrounded.
You can't win this war all by yourself. Gather allies who can support you in the battle against the Horde.
Before we can really take the fight to the Horde, we need to fortify our partnership with the Kul Tirans.
Before we can really take the fight to the Alliance, we first need to fortify our partnership with the people of Zandalar.
You can't win this war all by yourself. Gather followers who can support you in the battle against the Alliance.
We've found huge amounts of Azerite at sea! Captain Flynn Fairwind can take you there on his ship, the Middenwake.
We've found huge amounts of Azerite at sea! Captain Rez'okun can take you there on his ship, the Breath of Pa'ku.
The Dark Iron dwarves have set up camp in Zuldazar, near the Zandalari capital. They've discovered Azerite, and need your assistance securing the area.
Shadow Hunter Ty'jin has made contact with a mutinous pirate crew in Tiragarde Sound. This could be our foothold into the heart of Kul Tiras.
Our partnership with the Zandalari is progressing well. The Alliance, however, are cultivating their own partnership with Kul Tiras and their formidable army. This can't be allowed to happen.
Our partnership with Kul Tiras is progressing well. The Horde, however, are cultivating their own partnership with the Zandalari and their formidable army. This can't be allowed to happen.
Join Nathanos Blightcaller and Lilian Voss as they press into the heart of Tiragarde Sound.
The graveyards of Drustvar are filled with the corpses of fallen Kul Tiran war heroes. We could use these corpses... strategically.
The tidesages of Stormsong Valley have extraordinary power over the sea... power that we need.
Our first Horde VIP target is Arlethal Sunwatcher, a high-ranking member of the Reliquary. Taking him out will show the Horde that no one is safe from the Alliance, even across an ocean.
We now have the perfect bait to draw the Kul Tiran military away from their capital city of Boralus. This will buy us time to obtain our ultimate goal: the Abyssal Scepter.
Our second Horde VIP target is Ranger Captain Areiel, one of Warchief Sylvanas' most trusted dark rangers.
We're splitting up. Shandris will track down Blood Prince Dreven, while you and Magister Umbric deal with our third Horde VIP target: Trade Prince Gallywix.
The Horde's occupation of the Undercity must be ended! Today, we retake Lordaeron. For the Alliance!
The Alliance is advancing upon the Undercity! We will halt their incursion and crush their army. For the Horde!
We've intercepted a Horde missive, and learned that Blood Lord Dreven is currently aboard a Horde ship on the Great Sea. We've lost too many good men to Dreven. It's time to make him pay.

Name_lang: At the Bottom of the Sea
Description_lang: The body of a famous, long-dead Kul Tiran sea captain lies at the bottom of the Great Sea. Let's go check in on him.
We have the Horde on their heels. They're disarmed and disoriented after our targeted assassinations across Zandalar. Now's the time to strike the heart of the Zandalari Empire itself.
Magni bears a gift, but with it, terrible news: Azeroth is dying.
The Horde threaten the fortress of Stromgarde. Prepare for war in Lordaeron!
Alliance homefront forces are spread thin, and the fortress of Stromgarde is ripe for the taking. Prepare for war in Lordaeron!

Description_lang: Gallywix needs help fighting the Alliance using his mech of death, the G.M.O.D.

King Rastakhan is dead, and the Zandalari fleet is crippled. Lady Sylvanas Windrunner seems to have a plan to recover the Horde from defeat.

Name_lang: Beware the Daughter of the Sea
Description_lang: Lady Jaina Proudmoore is now Lord Admiral of Kul Tiras and needs help ensuring her home is safe from the Horde.
The Kul Tiran fleet is preparing to attack Zuldazar. To guarantee victory, the Alliance must create a distraction in Nazmir to lure away the armies of the Horde and Zandalari.
The Alliance have decimated the Zandalari fleet and killed King Rastakhan, but they have paid a heavy price.
Sylvanas Windrunner has ordered Priscilla Ashvane be broken out of Tol Dagor. She believes Ashvane has information critical to her master plan. There are also resources to be had.
The Horde have stolen the Abyssal Scepter, an artifact capable of destroying the Kul Tiran fleets. The Alliance must retrieve it to have any hope of attacking Zuldazar.
